name: Jasy Gwassu
description:
The moonbat goddess and her fireflies friends.

full moon
you saw me smiling alone
full of dreams in my heart
enjoying myself own 

"Jasy Gwassu" means full moon in Guarani, indigenous language from Latin America. Artwork in gouache and watercolor inspired by the little Diclidurus albus, also known as northern ghost bat.

From the Emballonuridae family, is insectivorous and found in Amazon and Atlantic Forest biomes. Present in the Brazilian states of Amapá, Amazonas, Bahia, Espírito Santo, Pará and Rondônia.

Piece made to #WitchingHourOnHEN

#HENHalloween #cen_halloween
